<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870402-0044 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Weatherford International Inc.</HL><DD> 04/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WIIEARNINGS (ERN) </IN><TEXT>   WEATHERFORD INTERNATIONAL INC., Houston, posted a narrowed fourth-quarter net loss of $3.6 million, compared with a loss of $11.3 million a year earlier, and said it entered into letters of intent with lenders to restructure about $41 million of its long-term debt. The oil-field equipment and services concern said fourth-quarter revenue declined 29% to $24.1 million from $34.1 million a year earlier. The year-earlier net loss included write-downs of $5.9 million. The company, which is in default under its major loan agreements, wouldn't disclose the names of its lenders. </TEXT></DOC>